Package io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2

Class IEEEDouble

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Number
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.IEEEDouble
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public final class IEEEDouble
extends java.lang.Number
Represents a Double value by its IEEE 754 hex value. This class enables accessing values computed by a solver with no loss of precision. This class uses the Apache Commons Math Precision class to implement equals and compareTo methods within a user-defined tolerance (default value 0.000001d). In all other ways, IEEEDouble values behave like ordinary Java Doubles.

      public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object obj)
      Tests the argument for equality with this number. Any type of argument except for Double or IEEE Double returns false. A proper argument returns equality within the tolerance (epsilon) for this number. Uses org.apache.commons.math3.util.Precision.equals(double, double, double);
      Overrides:
      equals in class java.lang.Object

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo​(IEEEDouble other)
      Compares this number to another. Returns the comparison within the tolerance (epsilon) for this number. Uses org.apache.commons.math3.util.Precision.compareTo(double, double, double).
      Parameters:
      other -
      Returns:
      • 0 if equals(x, y, eps)
      • < 0 if !equals(x, y, eps) & x < y
      • > 0 if !equals(x, y, eps) & x > y
